_f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n _r_e_t_u_r_n_s _t_h_e _o_r_i_e_n_t_a_t_i_o_n _o_f _a _b_r_a_i_n _i_m_a_g_e

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     generic function that returns a character string coding the
     orientation of a brain image

_U_s_a_g_e:

     orientation(x)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

       x: an object deriving from class "BrainSpace" or "BrainData" 

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     The orientation string encodes the anatomical direction of each of
     the (spatial) image axes.  Thus, a standard "neurologically"
     oriented image volume has the orientatrion string "LPI", whcih
     stands for "Left, Posterior, Inferior".  Currently this function
     is used only for information.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     character string representing image orientation

